{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-26T03:57:09.565Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1777175829564_0","parameters":{"file_path":"sdp/verification/t-021@20260425t183959zb-verify.md","content":"# Verification Report — T-021@20260425T183959Zb\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** 2026-04-26\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sample_status.py`\n- `my-claw/tools/face_display.py`\n- `tests/test_face_display_sample_status.py`\n- `tests/test_operator_diagnostics.py`\n- `specs/t-021@20260425t183959zb-spec.md`\n- `ESCALATIONS.md`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation correctly wires the combined sampler status line into the face display renderer. The new helper `face_display_sample_status_text` in `sample_status.py` successfully opts into the combined activity and playback wording by passing `combine_activity_and_playback=True` to `sample_status_text`. The face display renderer in `face_display.py` now uses this helper, ensuring that the face monitor mirrors the operator diagnostics.\n\n## Completeness\nAll acceptance criteria from the specification have been met:\n- The face-display sampler status helper combines plan and playback state when both are present.\n- The helper returns the plan-only phrase when playback is inactive but a plan is present.\n- The helper degrades cleanly to an empty string when all inputs are empty/missing and surfaces `monitor offline` when the monitor reports `no_capture`.\n- The face display renderer correctly imports and invokes the new combined helper in its sampler status block.\n\n## Consistency\nThe implementation follows established patterns:\n- The import in `face_display.py` includes a `try/except ImportError` fallback.\n- The formatting in `face_display.py` (font, color, placement) is preserved.\n- The logic remains consistent with the changes made in sub-task Za.\n\n## Security\nNo security vulnerabilities were identified. The changes are limited to diagnostic text formatting and do not involve any sensitive data or unsafe operations.\n\n## Quality\nThe code is clean, modular, and well-tested. The targeted tests for the new helper and the renderer wiring all pass. While some project-wide tests failed due to pre-existing environment issues (macOS seatbelt restrictions on `~/.promptclaw/pets.json`), these are unrelated to the current task and are consistent with previous reports.\n\n## Issues Found\n- [x] (Note) Pre-existing environment issues prevent some unrelated tests from running (`PermissionError` on `pets.json`), but this does not affect the verification of T-021.\n- [x] Hardening items regarding `bootstrap_identity` startup invocation are considered out of scope for this formatting task, as per the specification and established precedent in `ESCALATIONS.md`.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe implementation is solid and correctly fulfills the requirements. The face display now accurately reflects the combined sampler status, maintaining parity with operator diagnostics.\n"}}
